      "note": "Gooooood morning Snowbird! It’s Owen, with your snow report for Thursday. Mountain Update: 8 am - 2 pm spring lift operations will remain in place through Sunday, March 29. Hours of operation will be reassessed for the following week. Today is going to be sunny with a high of 52° and surf season is in full effect. The spring snow is ripping and the side hits are firing all over the mountain. I gotta say, it’s been pretty nice skiing in a t-shirt the past week or so, but I’ve definitely got a nice farmers tan going now so don’t be like me and remember your sunscreen. If you're looking for a good time this weekend, Plazapalooza starts tomorrow! Come check out The Wasatch Valley Drifters on the plaza deck tomorrow afternoon, and our other great bands in the days following. Bring your best party shirt. If you haven't yet gotten your Chickadee Fever badge on the Snowbird App, now's the time. The Chickadee Lift will close for the 2025-26 season for replacement on April 6th. The new Chickadee Lift is expected to reopen for summer operations in July. ALL uphill travel is closed. Don’t be that guy (or gal). Please remember to ski and ride in control, if you don’t, you’re gonna have a bad time.",
